comments_planning_coordination: Waiting to receive funds, IPFs, and guidance from MoH Unepi; the monthly coordination meetings have not started
comments_training: Common myths and misconceptions about vaccine; communities have expressed concerns about the increased number of injectable vaccines. It is important to deliver IEC materials before training is conducted.
comments_m_e: MVI IPF and guidelines should be shared urgently to guide supervision plans.
vaccines_mgt_supplied_comments_cold_chai: Majority of health facilities use open pit burning. Green label supported retrieval and final disposal. Need to deliver the MVI vaccine and related supplies soonest as the introduction date is so close.
comments_advocacy_communication: Central payments for ACSM activities always delay or even never paid. As a result, districts are hesitant to commit to initiating ACSM activities with assurance. Secondly, service providers are not comfortable as previous payments have not been effected. None of 5 persons interviewed had heard about Malaria Vaccine introduction
overall_comments: The district is not on track to conduct MVI in April 2025 unless IEC materials, IPFs, and guidelines as well as funds are delivered/disbursed immeidately to faxiliate planning, social mobilization and training. Generally, the districts are enthusiastic about the introduction of a malaria vaccine. They are, however, concerned about the delays in communication and preparing districts.

comments_planning_coordination: Districts needs to further clean the microplans, especially regarding the identification of resistant communities. The coordination committee established but needs activation towards MVI implementation. MoH needs to disburse funds; anticipated delays in cash limit and processing supplementary funds through Council, MOH should immediately share IPFs and guidelines
comments_training: Rampant myths and misconceptions about vaccines, community fears around multiple injections, need to plan for sufficient periods for training. One day is not enough, IEC materials should be delivered ahead of time so they can be used during training as well.
comments_m_e: MOH to share IPFs so that realistic supervision plans are developed
vaccines_mgt_supplied_comments_cold_chai: 21 cold boxes, but 11 are phased out and are non functional. Close to 401 vaccine carriers, but 150 are damaged. Limited storage space for cold boxes and vaccine carriers as a result of the district having a small DVS. NMS to deliver vaccines and supplies sooner as well as dispatch teams to support cold chain maintenance before the introduction.
comments_advocacy_communication: MoH to share IEC materials soonest. The communities were not yet aware of the MVI as only 2 out of 5 interviewed reported that they had heard. Moreover, they couldn't remember the date and venues mentioned in the messages they heard.
overall_comments: The district is not on track to conduct MVI in April 2025 unless IEC materials, IPFs, and guidelines as well as funds are delivered/disbursed immeidately to faxiliate planning, social mobilization and training. Generally, the districts are enthusiastic about the introduction of a malaria vaccine. They are, however, concerned about the delays in communication and preparing districts.

comments_advocacy_communication: Central payments for ACSM activities always delay or even never paid. As a result, districts are hesitant to commit to initiating ACSM activities with assurance. Secondly, service providers are not comfortable as previous payments have not been effected. None of 5 persons interviewed had heard about Malaria Vaccine introduction
overall_comments: The district is not on track to conduct MVI in April 2025 unless IEC materials, IPFs, and guidelines as well as funds are delivered/disbursed immeidately to faxiliate planning, social mobilization and training. Generally, the districts are enthusiastic about the introduction of a malaria vaccine. They are, however, concerned about the delays in communication and preparing districts.

comments_planning_coordination: Districts needs to further clean the microplans, especially regarding the identification of resistant communities. The coordination committee established but needs activation towards MVI implementation. MoH needs to disburse funds; anticipated delays in cash limit and processing supplementary funds through Council, MOH should immediately share IPFs and guidelines
comments_training: Rampant myths and misconceptions about vaccines, community fears around multiple injections, need to plan for sufficient periods for training. One day is not enough, IEC materials should be delivered ahead of time so they can be used during training as well.
comments_m_e: MOH to share IPFs so that realistic supervision plans are developed
vaccines_mgt_supplied_comments_cold_chai: 21 cold boxes, but 11 are phased out and are non functional. Close to 401 vaccine carriers, but 150 are damaged. Limited storage space for cold boxes and vaccine carriers as a result of the district having a small DVS. NMS to deliver vaccines and supplies sooner as well as dispatch teams to support cold chain maintenance before the introduction.
comments_advocacy_communication: MoH to share IEC materials soonest. The communities were not yet aware of the MVI as only 2 out of 5 interviewed reported that they had heard. Moreover, they couldn't remember the date and venues mentioned in the messages they heard.
overall_comments: The district is not on track to conduct MVI in April 2025 unless IEC materials, IPFs, and guidelines as well as funds are delivered/disbursed immeidately to faxiliate planning, social mobilization and training. Generally, the districts are enthusiastic about the introduction of a malaria vaccine. They are, however, concerned about the delays in communication and preparing districts.

comments_planning_coordination: Waiting to receive funds, IPFs, and guidance from MoH Unepi; the monthly coordination meetings have not started
comments_training: Common myths and misconceptions about vaccine; communities have expressed concerns about the increased number of injectable vaccines. It is important to deliver IEC materials before training is conducted.
comments_m_e: MVI IPF and guidelines should be shared urgently to guide supervision plans.
vaccines_mgt_supplied_comments_cold_chai: Majority of health facilities use open pit burning. Green label supported retrieval and final disposal. Need to deliver the MVI vaccine and related supplies soonest as the introduction date is so close.
comments_advocacy_communication: Central payments for ACSM activities always delay or even never paid. As a result, districts are hesitant to commit to initiating ACSM activities with assurance. Secondly, service providers are not comfortable as previous payments have not been effected. None of 5 persons interviewed had heard about Malaria Vaccine introduction
overall_comments: The district is not on track to conduct MVI in April 2025 unless IEC materials, IPFs, and guidelines as well as funds are delivered/disbursed immeidately to faxiliate planning, social mobilization and training. Generally, the districts are enthusiastic about the introduction of a malaria vaccine. They are, however, concerned about the delays in communication and preparing districts.

comments_planning_coordination: Districts needs to further clean the microplans, especially regarding the identification of resistant communities. The coordination committee established but needs activation towards MVI implementation. MoH needs to disburse funds; anticipated delays in cash limit and processing supplementary funds through Council, MOH should immediately share IPFs and guidelines
comments_training: Rampant myths and misconceptions about vaccines, community fears around multiple injections, need to plan for sufficient periods for training. One day is not enough, IEC materials should be delivered ahead of time so they can be used during training as well.
comments_m_e: MOH to share IPFs so that realistic supervision plans are developed
vaccines_mgt_supplied_comments_cold_chai: 21 cold boxes, but 11 are phased out and are non functional. Close to 401 vaccine carriers, but 150 are damaged. Limited storage space for cold boxes and vaccine carriers as a result of the district having a small DVS. NMS to deliver vaccines and supplies sooner as well as dispatch teams to support cold chain maintenance before the introduction.
comments_advocacy_communication: MoH to share IEC materials soonest. The communities were not yet aware of the MVI as only 2 out of 5 interviewed reported that they had heard. Moreover, they couldn't remember the date and venues mentioned in the messages they heard.
overall_comments: The district is not on track to conduct MVI in April 2025 unless IEC materials, IPFs, and guidelines as well as funds are delivered/disbursed immeidately to faxiliate planning, social mobilization and training. Generally, the districts are enthusiastic about the introduction of a malaria vaccine. They are, however, concerned about the delays in communication and preparing districts.

overall_comments:
1. Sharing the MVI activity budget early enough to enable adequate planning
2. Rely on contextual categorization of hard to reach areas to improve coverage.
3. Plan for adequate facilitation of VHTs (most effective) proportionate to the amount of money they spend from their locations: For example, those from Lolelia, Napeikar, Kaalale- Spend between 30,000-40,000Ugsh for a complete journey from and to the usual training sites. Compensating them with 10,000 is always very demoralizing and unreasonable.
4. Plan for refreshments during trainings to ensure that participants retention rather than loosing some due to hunger.
5. Supply data tools based on the demand from district rather than using estimations.
5. Incentivise report compilation either with an Airtime package or SDA for efficient accountability processes. e-Payments downside effect; as those who compile reports are less motivated to do so

comments_planning_coordination:
1) Programs should be re-scheduled well so that they don't collide.
2) Ministry should involve district technical people during implementation of activities and also equip them with technical knowledge.
3) IEC materials should be delivered earlier so that information can be disseminated easily and timely to the communities.
comments_training:
1) Adequate time for training should be availed.
2) More training time should be allocated to stakeholders.
3) IEC materials should be provided adequately and timely.
4) Practical sessions should be enhanced to allow grasping of concepts.
comments_m_e:
1) Adequate tools should be supplied and also on a timely basis.
2) EPI focal persons should be well equiped with knowledge.
vaccines_mgt_supplied_comments_cold_chai:
1) The faulty fridge should be fixed. 
2) Need to know the quantity of the vaccines visa vi the size of the fridges available.

comments_advocacy_communication:
1) IEC materials should be availed on time.
2) Revise number of days for mobilization. They need to be increased.
3) Need to come up with a bottom up strategy for mobilization.
overall_comments:
1) IEC materials should be availed on time.
2) On the side of cold chain, fuel should be sent earlier for easy transportation of logistics. Vaccines should also be brought on time to the DVS.
3) on the M&E side , enough tools for data capture should be availed. orient HIAs on how to pick data.
4) On the area of planning, prior assessment should be done. 
5) Guidelines should be availed early so that stakeholders are in the know.
6) Key stakeholders should be involved on record time.
7) The district council should be brought on board and facilitated for easy mobilization.
8) Equitable distribution of RDC airtime for easy mobilization.
